com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.textured

Class CustomTexturedTool

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.CustomItem
      • com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.CustomTool
        • com.chrismin13.additionsapi.items.textured.CustomTexturedTool
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, Comparable<CustomItem>, ModelInjector

    public class CustomTexturedTool
extends CustomTool
implements ModelInjector
    A CustomTool that contains at least one Texture since it implements ModelInjector. A texture pack is required in order for the Item to function. The Texture Pack will be provided during the AdditionsAPIInitializationEvent using the AdditionsAPIInitializationEvent.addResourcePackFromPlugin(org.bukkit.plugin.java.JavaPlugin, String) or a similar method. The resource pack must have the following structure: assets\plugin_name\textures\items\texture_name.png where plugin_name will be the first part of the CustomTool's Id Name (e.g. "vanilla_additions") and the texture_name will be the name of the Texture that you specified when creating the Item. It is necessary that the CustomTexturedTool is registered during the AdditionsAPIInitializationEvent and that the Texture Pack is received by the Player in order for the Texture to work.
    The main difference between a CustomTexturedTool and a CustomTexturedItem is that the CustomTexturedTool will appear as handheld, so that the stick part lines up with the hand of the player, as seen with Swords, Axes, Pickaxes, Shovels and Hoes in-game.
    Author:
    chrismin13

    • Constructor Detail

      • CustomTexturedTool

        public CustomTexturedTool(DamageableItem dItem,
                          String idName,
                          String defaultTexture)
        Creates a CustomTexturedTool
        Parameters:
        dItem - The DamageableItem that the CustomTool will be based off. This will determine the Material of the CustomTool.
        idName - the CustomTool's ID Name. This MUST BE SIMILAR to "vanilla_additions:emerald_sword" as the Texture will not be able to be detected otherwise. It is also saved in the ItemStack so you can easily detect which CustomTool it is.
        defaultTexture - The name of the default texture. This will be the name of the PNG file (without the extension .png) whose texture will be used from the Resource Pack.

      • getOverrideEntries

        public HashMap<ModelInjection,Short> getOverrideEntries()
        Description copied from interface: ModelInjector

        Provide your override entry to define the model that you want to use.
        The "damaged" and "damage" tag will be automatically defined by the toolbox, you don't need to worry about them.

        Note: You should at least provide an entry with a empty predicate tag that points to your basic model

        Specified by:
        getOverrideEntries in interface ModelInjector
        Returns:
        A list of override entries that need to be injected into the base model.

        -- The base model is the original item's model, we inject a override entry so it will display the model we defined when an itemstack matches our custom item id.
